<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-20T11:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-20T11:49:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.002/4.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-20T12:00:00-04:49"><hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi>
                                    20, 1911—12 <hi rend="smallcaps">noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The minister reports cabinet changes that will further injure status of
                            the present administration. He was advised yesterday by the Haitian
                            Government that the cities of St. Marc and Gonaives would be bombarded;
                            he protested against such action unless carried out in accordance with
                            The Hague convention.</p>
                    </div>
